[
    {
        "content": "<p>Suppose I have a lean project I'm working on, which I do not intend ever integrating with mathlib. Suppose also that I want to use a (non-master) branch of mathlib in this project. What's the preferred workflow to accomplish this? Does <code>leanproject</code> have a flag that will create a project based importing a non-master branch of mathlib?</p>",
        "id": 223660241,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1611331220
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally, I would just manually lump the commit hash of mathlib into the <code>leanpkg.toml</code></p>",
        "id": 223660329,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1611331264
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And don't run <code>leanproject up</code></p>",
        "id": 223660380,
        "sender_full_name": "Rob Lewis",
        "timestamp": 1611331287
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay. So how would I use leanproject to get the oleans for the particular hash?</p>",
        "id": 223660449,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1611331318
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>leanproject get-mathlib-cache</code></p>",
        "id": 223660515,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1611331329
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is it <code>leanproject get-mathlib-cache</code>?</p>",
        "id": 223660520,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1611331331
    },
    {
